This paper deals with a random graph model that has applications in secure sensor networks and social networks, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses connectivity in the graph, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents a zero-one law, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM and cs.SI, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.IT.
